Kconfig tools
=============

You can use this in your kconfig based build system. This is just a simple implementation.


Build:
------

1. Navigate to the root directory of this repository.
2. Run 'make' to build all the tools:

$ make

To build a specific tool, run 'make <tool_name>'.

   For example, to build only the 'conf' tool, run:

$ make conf

Clean Instructions:
-------------------

To start fresh you can run:

$ make clean

Testing
-------

To test one of the built binaries, you can run any *conf following command. For example:

$ ./kconfig/mconf Kconfig.test # for menuconfig
$ ./kconfig/nconf Kconfig.test # for nconfig
$ ./kconfig/gconf Kconfig.test # for gconfig
$ ./kconfig/qconf Kconfig.test # for xconfig
$ ./kconfig/conf Kconfig.test  # for config

Credits
-------

Linux kernel authors - Original Kconfig system 
